                    <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-8">
                        <p>
                            Your privacy is critically important to us. At FindIt, we have a few fundamental principles:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 marker:text-primary">
                            <li>We don't ask you for personal information unless we truly need it.</li>
                            <li>We don't share your personal information with anyone except to comply with the law, develop our products, or protect our rights.</li>
                            <li>We don't store personal information on our servers unless required for the on-going operation of one of our services.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-text-main dark:text-white mt-8 mb-2">Data We Collect</h3>
                        <p>
                            When you register for an account, we may ask for your contact information, including items such as name, company name, address, email address, and telephone number. If you list an item as lost or found, we collect the details of that item including location data to help facilitate the search.
                        </p>
                        <div class="p-4 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-900/10 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 rounded-r-lg">
                            <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800 dark:text-yellow-200">
                                <strong>Note:</strong> We never publicly display your exact home address. Location data is generalized for safety.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
                <section class="scroll-mt-24" id="terms">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
                        <div class="p-2 bg-emerald-500/10 rounded-lg text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">
